children.name: onBlur
children.comment: Event fires when an element has lost focus. The main difference between this event and focusout is that focusout bubbles while blur does not.

children.name: onClick
children.comment: An element receives a click event when a pointing device button (such as a mouse's primary mouse button) is both pressed and released while the pointer is located inside the element.

children.name: onFocus
children.comment: Event fires when an element has received focus. The main difference between this event and focusin is that focusin bubbles while focus does not.

children.name: onKeyDown
children.comment: Event is fired when a key is pressed.

children.name: onKeyPress
children.comment: Event is fired when a key that produces a character value is pressed down. Examples of keys that produce a character value are alphabetic, numeric, and punctuation keys.

children.name: onMouseEnter
children.comment: Event is fired at an Element when a pointing device (usually a mouse) is initially moved so that its hotspot is within the element at which the event was fired.

children.name: onMouseLeave
children.comment: Event is fired at an Element when the cursor of a pointing device (usually a mouse) is moved out of it.

children.name: onMouseUp
children.comment: Event is fired at an Element when a button on a pointing device (such as a mouse or trackpad) is released while the pointer is located inside it. mouseup events are the counterpoint to onMouseDown events.

children.name: onTouchEnd
children.comment: Event fires when one or more touch points are removed from the touch surface.

children.name: onTouchStart
children.comment: Event is fired when one or more touch points are placed on the touch surface.

children.name: alignSelf
children.comment: Property overrides a grid or flex item's align-items value. In Grid, it aligns the item inside the grid area. In Flexbox, it aligns the item on the cross axis.

children.name: flex
children.comment: Sets how a flex item will grow or shrink to fit the space available in its flex container.

children.name: flexBasis
children.comment: Sets the initial main size of a flex item. It sets the size of the content box unless otherwise set with box-sizing.

children.name: flexGrow
children.comment: Sets the flex grow factor of a flex item main size. It specifies how much of the remaining space in the flex container should be assigned to the item (the flex grow factor).

children.name: flexShrink
children.comment: Sets the flex shrink factor of a flex item. If the size of all flex items is larger than the flex container, items shrink to fit according to flex-shrink.

children.name: justifySelf
children.comment: Sets the way a box is justified inside its alignment container along the appropriate axis.

children.name: gridArea
children.comment: Shorthand property for grid-row-start, grid-column-start, grid-row-end and grid-column-end, specifying a grid items size and location within the grid by contributing a line, a span, or nothing (automatic) to its grid placement, thereby specifying the edges of its grid area.

children.name: gridColumn
children.comment: Shorthand property for grid-column-start and grid-column-end specifying a grid item's size and location within the grid column by contributing a line, a span, or nothing (automatic) to its grid placement, thereby specifying the inline-start and inline-end edge of its grid area.

children.name: gridColumnEnd
children.comment: Specifies a grid items end position within the grid column by contributing a line, a span, or nothing (automatic) to its grid placement, thereby specifying the block-end edge of its grid area.

children.name: gridColumnStart
children.comment: Specifies a grid items start position within the grid column by contributing a line, a span, or nothing (automatic) to its grid placement. This start position defines the block-start edge of the grid area.

children.name: gridRow
children.comment: Shorthand property for grid-row-start and grid-row-end specifying a grid items size and location within the grid row by contributing a line, a span, or nothing (automatic) to its grid placement, thereby specifying the inline-start and inline-end edge of its grid area.

children.name: gridRowEnd
children.comment: Specifies a grid items end position within the grid row by contributing a line, a span, or nothing (automatic) to its grid placement, thereby specifying the inline-end edge of its grid area.

children.name: gridRowStart
children.comment: Specifies a grid items start position within the grid row by contributing a line, a span, or nothing (automatic) to its grid placement, thereby specifying the inline-start edge of its grid area.

children.name: placeSelf
children.comment: Shorthand property sets both the align-self and justify-self properties. The first value is the align-self property value, the second the justify-self one. If the second value is not present, the first value is also used for it.

children.name: flex
children.comment: Sets how a flex item will grow or shrink to fit the space available in its flex container.

children.name: flexBasis
children.comment: Sets the initial main size of a flex item. It sets the size of the content box unless otherwise set with box-sizing.

children.name: flexGrow
children.comment: Sets the flex grow factor of a flex item main size. It specifies how much of the remaining space in the flex container should be assigned to the item (the flex grow factor).

children.name: flexShrink
children.comment: Sets the flex shrink factor of a flex item. If the size of all flex items is larger than the flex container, items shrink to fit according to flex-shrink.

children.name: justifySelf
children.comment: Sets the way a box is justified inside its alignment container along the appropriate axis.

children.name: gridArea

children.name: gridColumnStart

children.name: gridRow

children.comment: Event is fired when a key that produces a character value is pressed down. Examples of keys that produce a character value are alphabetic, numeric, and punctuation keys.

children.comment: Event is fired when a key is released.

children.name: onMouseDown
children.comment: Event is fired at an Element when a pointing device button is pressed while the pointer is inside the element.

children.name: onMouseEnter
children.comment: Event is fired at an Element when a pointing device (usually a mouse) is initially moved so that its hotspot is within the element at which the event was fired.

children.name: onMouseLeave
children.comment: Event is fired at an Element when the cursor of a pointing device (usually a mouse) is moved out of it.

children.name: onMouseUp
children.comment: Event is fired at an Element when a button on a pointing device (such as a mouse or trackpad) is released while the pointer is located inside it. mouseup events are the counterpoint to onMouseDown events.

children.name: onTouchEnd
children.comment: Event fires when one or more touch points are removed from the touch surface.

children.name: onTouchStart
children.comment: Event is fired when one or more touch points are placed on the touch surface.

children.name: onBlur
children.comment: Event fires when an element has lost focus. The main difference between this event and focusout is that focusout bubbles while blur does not.

children.name: onClick
children.comment: An element receives a click event when a pointing device button (such as a mouse's primary mouse button) is both pressed and released while the pointer is located inside the element.

children.name: onFocus
children.comment: Event fires when an element has received focus. The main difference between this event and focusin is that focusin bubbles while focus does not.

children.name: onKeyDown
children.comment: Event is fired when a key is pressed.

children.name: onKeyPress
children.comment: Event is fired when a key that produces a character value is pressed down. Examples of keys that produce a character value are alphabetic, numeric, and punctuation keys.
